(constant) Types

provides safe type checking functions: isFunction, isArray, isObject, isNull, isUndefined, isBoolean, isNumber, isString

Source:
  • types.js, line 20
Example
isFunction(text => console.log(text)) // returns true
isBoolean('true') // returns false
